  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Precision Assembly Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assemble mechanical and electro-mechanical components according to assembly drawings and work instructions</li><li>Develop assembly and test procedures to promote production of quality products</li><li>Perform cleaning of all parts as per established cleaning procedures</li><li>Perform pre-assembly activities such as cleaning and lubricating</li><li>Conduct product testing and performance testing and record the results</li><li>Perform final checks and adjustments for any defects to ensure high quality products</li><li>Perform installation, repair, inspect, reassembly, replacing, refitting, and adjusting products as required</li><li>Receive, unload, unpack and transfer materials to different work stations</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or NITEC or ITC level qualification in Mechanical/Electric engineering or equivalent</li><li>Able to read electro-mechanical drawings</li><li>Experience in machine production/assembly environment</li><li>Independent and have initiative with committed working attitude</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li></ul><p><strong>Job Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>5 days work week</li><li>Group Medical Insurance</li><li>OT Claim where applicable</li></ul>",
